where
formula_39

===Spherical and hyperbolic geometry===
L&#x27;Huilier&#x27;s formula relates the area of a triangle in spherical geometry to its side lengths. For a spherical triangle with side lengths and , semiperimeter , and area ,
formula_40

For a triangle in hyperbolic geometry the analogous formula is
formula_41

