A set of sides that can form a cyclic quadrilateral can be arranged in any of three distinct sequences each of which can form a cyclic quadrilateral of the same area in the same circumcircle (the areas being the same according to Brahmagupta&#x27;s area formula). Any two of these cyclic quadrilaterals have one diagonal length in common.

